{
  "id": "c0c0c0c0-0001-0000-0000-000000000000",
  "name": "Kernel",
  "type": "871ae771-b9b1-4f40-8c7f-d9038bfb69c3",
  "created": 1738454400000,
  "modified": 1773334564066,
  "content": {
    "description": [
      ":doc",
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The kernel is Hobson's minimal runtime—the smallest possible core that enables everything else to be built as items."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Philosophy"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The kernel follows a "
        },
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "minimal design"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " principle: it provides only what cannot be implemented as userland items. Everything else—views, editors, error handling, search—lives outside the kernel as regular items that can be inspected, modified, or replaced."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "What the Kernel Does"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":table",
        [
          ":thead",
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":th",
              {
                "s": "Responsibility"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":th",
              {
                "s": "Why It Must Be Kernel"
              }
            ]
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":tbody",
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":strong",
                {
                  "s": "Storage"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Items need somewhere to live before items can define storage"
              }
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":strong",
                {
                  "s": "Type validation"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Must validate type chains before items can run"
              }
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":strong",
                {
                  "s": "Code execution"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Must load code items before code items can load other code"
              }
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":strong",
                {
                  "s": "Bootstrap"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Must initialize the system before system items exist"
              }
            ]
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "The Kernel Modules"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The kernel is decomposed into cohesive modules, each stored as an item:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "const modules = await api.query({ type: api.IDS.KERNEL_MODULE });\nmodules.sort((a, b) => (a.name || '').localeCompare(b.name || ''));\nconst rows = modules.map(m => {\n  const desc = m.content?.description?.split('\\n')[0] || 'No description';\n  return `| [${m.name}](item://${m.id}) | ${desc} |`;\n});\nreturn '| Module | Purpose |\\n|--------|---------|\\n' + rows.join('\\n') + '\\n';"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "What's NOT in the Kernel"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "These are implemented as userland items:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Error handling"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — "
            },
            [
              ":item-ref",
              {
                "s": "e7707000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002"
              },
              {
                "s": "default-error-handler"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " creates error items"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Selection"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — "
            },
            [
              ":item-ref",
              {
                "s": "f1111111-0001-0000-0000-000000000000"
              },
              {
                "s": "selection-manager"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " tracks selected items"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Item search"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — Libraries and views, not kernel code"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Document rendering"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — "
            },
            {
              "s": "doc-ast-renderer"
            },
            {
              "s": " library"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "All views"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — Even the viewport view is technically userland"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "All type definitions"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — Types like "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "note"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ", "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "container"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ", "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "tag"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " are items"
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Self-Modification"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Because kernel modules are items, you can:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Read their source code"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Link to specific functions via "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "item://id#code?region=name"
              }
            ]
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "(Carefully) modify kernel behavior"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Replace modules with custom implementations"
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Warning:"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " Editing kernel modules can break your system. Use "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "33333333-7777-0000-0000-000000000000"
          },
          {
            "s": "safe mode"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " to recover."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Design Rationale"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Why Minimal?"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The kernel follows the principle: if it can be built as a userland item, it should be. This means:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Less kernel code to break"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "More of the system is inspectable and modifiable"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Features can be upgraded without touching the kernel"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "The system increasingly defines itself in terms of itself"
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Why Always-On?"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Hobson embodies the \\\"always on\\\" principle from Conway's Humane Dozen. The app runs continuously (like Smalltalk) — no start/stop cycle. Modifying a code item changes running behavior immediately."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Lifecycle Hooks"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The kernel manages automatic subscriptions: when a view renders an item, the kernel subscribes to changes in that item's attachments. When a child changes, the kernel calls the parent's lifecycle hooks (if defined) and automatically re-renders. See "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "c0c0c0c0-0006-0000-0000-000000000000"
          },
          {
            "s": "Event System"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " for details."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "See Also"
        }
      ],
      [
